Project Overview

This project demonstrates the use of Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) for dimensionality reduction on text data to automatically discover latent topics from a collection of news articles. The approach leverages Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) to extract compact topic representations, which can then support clustering or classification tasks.

The project uses the 20 Newsgroups dataset as an example corpus, focusing on selected categories.

Problem Statement

A news aggregator wants to automatically identify latent topics from a large collection of articles. The goal is to:

Transform text data into numerical form using TF-IDF vectorization.
Reduce dimensionality using Truncated SVD.
Extract and interpret latent topics.
Evaluate the effectiveness of reduced representations for classification.
Dataset

The project uses the 20 Newsgroups dataset, available through scikit-learn.

Selected example categories for demonstration:

sci.space
rec.autos
talk.politics.misc

Source: scikit-learn 20 Newsgroups dataset

Implementation Steps
1)Data Cleaning
    Remove missing (NaN) documents.
    Optional: remove headers, footers, and quotes from raw text.
2)TF-IDF Vectorization
    Converts text documents into numerical feature vectors.
    Stopwords are removed to reduce noise.
3)Dimensionality Reduction with SVD (LSA)
    Apply TruncatedSVD with multiple component settings (e.g., 50, 100, 200).
    Extract latent topics and interpret top 10 terms per topic.
    Calculate explained variance to evaluate information retention.
4)Classification Evaluation (Optional)
    Use the reduced features to train a Logistic Regression classifier.
    Measure accuracy to check how well reduced features preserve information.
5)Visualization
    Plot explained variance vs number of components.
    Plot classification accuracy vs number of components (if classification is performed).
    Optional: generate word clouds for top terms of each topic.
6)Save Results
    20newsgroups_subset.csv → cleaned dataset
    lsa_topic_terms.txt → top 10 terms for first 5 topics
    svd_results.csv → components, explained variance, classification accuracy
